Common clothing styles and amount of hats depdening on the weather

Clothing styles everyday of the Week

The first plot showcases the distribution of time stamps. This visualization is used to show how many times each type of clothing style was logged on each da of the week. It seems people dress casual on Tuesdays, a weekday, and more Y2k, out-there during weekends.

This second plot is sued to show the relationship between weather and clothing style. Aiming to figure out if there is a relationship between these two variables. Based on the graph, it seems as though people are more likely to wear casual and comfortable outfits consisting of t-shirts and pants. On warmer days, people are dressing in a more Y2K fashion style. Most likely because Y2K outfits feature articles of clothing such as crop tops, miniskirts and low rise bottoms.
